  • Class
    Description
    Account
    The account class represents a bank account with an account number, account holder and an account balance.
    AccountDatabase
    The AccountDatabase class manages a collection of bank accounts, allowing addition, removal, and transactions.
    AccountNumber
    The AccountNumber class represents a unique account identifier that contains a branch code, an account type and a randomly generated 4-digit number.
    AccountType
    This is an enum class for the account types users can pick from which include: checking, savings and money market savings.
    Activity
    The Activity class shows the transaction activity associated with each bank account.
    Archive
    This class implements a linked list that holds a list of closed accounts, includes adding and printing
    Branch
    This is an enum class for the branches of New Jersey that includes the zip, branchCode and county variables.
    Campus
    This enum class assigns a number that corresponds to the campus type.
    CertificateDeposit
    The Certificate Deposit account type class that extends the Savings class.
    Checking
    The Checking account subclass extends the Account class.
    CollegeChecking
    The CollegeChecking account type class that extends the checking class also determines whether a user is eligible to open.
    MoneyMarket
    The MoneyMarket account subclass extends the Savings class.
    Profile
    The profile class represents a user profile with first name, last name and date of birth.
    Savings
    The Savings account subclass extends the Account class.
